&lt;p&gt;At Precision AQ, our Associate Program Managers play a critical role in bringing client programs to life—ensuring projects run smoothly, deadlines are met, and teams stay aligned every step of the way. This is an exciting opportunity to work at the intersection of healthcare, communication, and project management, collaborating with cross-functional teams and clients to deliver meaningful results. You’ll gain exposure to a variety of projects, build strong client relationships, and grow your expertise within a fast-paced, collaborative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are highly organized and thrive in managing multiple projects and competing priorities simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a strong communicator who feels confident interfacing with both internal teams and external clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are detail-oriented and proactive, with the ability to identify challenges and implement solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy working in a fast-paced, collaborative environment where no two days look the same&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable balancing logistics, timelines, and budgets while keeping stakeholders aligned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are interested in growing your career in program or project management within a healthcare or agency setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Program Manager, you will support the successful execution of client programs by managing timelines, workflows, and project deliverables. Working under the guidance of a Program Director or Program Manager, you will act as a central point of coordination across internal teams, clients, and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your day-to-day, you will oversee project workflows, facilitate internal and client meetings, and ensure that deliverables progress on schedule. You will also help manage medical/legal/regulatory (MLR) submissions, coordinate with vendors, and support financial tracking, including budgets and invoicing. Additionally, you will have the opportunity to independently lead smaller projects while mentoring junior team members and contributing to overall team success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–3 years of experience in a client service, agency, or project coordination environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent relevant work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience managing multiple projects and timelines simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Helpful Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting medical/legal/regulatory (MLR) processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to budgeting or financial tracking for client projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience coordinating events, meetings, or program logistics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with vendor or agency partner management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Precision AQ - Medical Communications was founded with the simple belief that the scientific story is the foundation of every pharmaceutical brand. Our teams of inquisitive problem solvers and passionate creators dig deep to translate the science behind today’s cutting-edge therapies, then communicate the science clearly and credibly. Our proven track record of long-tenured relationships with major pharmaceutical companies and leading bio-tech firms, and our inclusive, open-minded team culture are industry leading. This passionate work environment, paired with growth opportunity, professional dev

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate Research Scientist – Evidence Generation (Primary Data Collection)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to work with a dynamic team of industry leading professionals in the HEOR space? Is your passion leading research studies that improve healthcare outcomes worldwide? Our&lt;strong&gt; Evidence Generation team is hiring an Associate Research Scientist &lt;/strong&gt;to join our team of research professionals conducting primary data collection studies in the pharmaceutical and biotech space; contributing to study execution, problem solving, and supporting both qualitative and quantitative data collection and analysis efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have an interest in health economics and outcomes research and a basic understanding of the pharmaceutical industry and medical affairs, with a willingness to learn how to identify client needs and considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience supporting activities that contribute to collecting data from multiple types of stakeholders in the healthcare ecosystem: patients, caregivers, providers, payers and policy makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience conducting literature reviews, scientific writing, supporting data synthesis and interpretation, and deliverable creation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience in qualitative and quantitative data collection and analysis tasks, including supporting the development of data collection materials (e.g., surveys, interview discussion guides), &amp;nbsp;familiarity with qualitative analysis software (e.g., NVivo, Dedoose) and quantitative programs (e.g., Excel, R, SAS, or Stata), and experience with qualitative and quantitative data interpretation and visualization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You assist with the implementation of research plans and methodologies, working closely with team members to support study execution and project coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong verbal and visual communication skills and can support the development of client-ready presentation materials (e.g., slide decks) to convey insights to internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Research Scientist on the Evidence Generation team, you will contribute to multiple projects, working with cross-functional teams across mixed-methods research approaches and a range of therapeutic areas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Study Execution&lt;/strong&gt;: Support all aspects of execution of primary data collection research studies, including literature reviews; development of data collection instruments (e.g., surveys, interview guides); study protocols; data collection; data analysis and interpretation; and support dissemination activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliverable Creation&lt;/strong&gt;: Contribute to the development of project deliverables under the guidance of senior team members with methodological and subject matter expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management&lt;/strong&gt;: Assist with the delivery of project components by collaborating with team members to ensure high-quality outputs and help maintain project timelines for assigned tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Management&lt;/strong&gt;: Support client engagement activities by drafting update slides for regular client meetings with guidance from senior team members, and documenting meeting notes, action items, and next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development&lt;/strong&gt;: Contribute to proposal and presentation development by drafting background sections, task descriptions, timelines, and references with guidance from senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;u

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about translating cutting-edge science into meaningful outcomes for patients? Join a collaborative, high-performing medical communications team where your scientific expertise directly informs impactful programs for leading pharmaceutical and biotech clients. In this role, you’ll partner across disciplines to shape strategy, elevate scientific storytelling, and contribute to a culture built on excellence, innovation, and long-standing client success. This is an opportunity to grow within a dynamic organization known for its award-winning work, strong client partnerships, and commitment to professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are energized by interpreting complex scientific data and transforming it into clear, compelling communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in a collaborative, cross-functional environment and enjoy partnering with clients, authors, and internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring strong leadership instincts and enjoy mentoring writers while elevating team output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are highly detail-oriented with a commitment to scientific accuracy and editorial excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You stay curious—actively following emerging research, competitive landscapes, and therapeutic advancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are confident presenting scientific perspectives to clients, key opinion leaders, and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Scientific Director, you will play a central role in ensuring all deliverables are evidence-based, strategically aligned, and executed with the highest level of quality. You will partner closely with a Scientific Director and Strategic Account Directors to translate client objectives into impactful scientific content and programs. Acting as both a content expert and team leader, you will guide medical writers, oversee the quality-control process, and contribute to strategic planning across projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will engage directly with clients, authors, and key opinion leaders, helping shape scientific narratives across therapeutic areas. You’ll contribute to content development, regulatory review, and advisory board planning, while also identifying opportunities for innovation and business growth. Your work will directly support the delivery of strategic medical communications solutions that enhance clinical understanding and patient outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced life sciences degree (MD, PhD, or PharmD)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–3+ years of experience within a medical communications agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated expertise in medical/scientific writing and content development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage multiple projects and timelines in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating with clients, key opinion leaders, and cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Helpful Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience mentoring or managing medical writers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to regulatory review processes and advisory board development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with competitive intelligence and therapeutic landscape analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting new business development or client growth initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
