&lt;p&gt;The People Operations Partner provides in-country-specific HR operational expertise within the global HR operating model. Acting as the Tier 2 operational HR lead for their assigned country, the role manages complex employee lifecycle activity, local legislative requirements, employee relations support, and operational implementation of HR processes and business change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role serves as the primary operational HR expert for managers, HRBPs, Payroll, Legal and COEs on country-specific employment practices, compliance requirements, and operational people matters. The position ensures global HR processes are delivered effectively while remaining compliant with local legislation and market practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is distinct from Global People Services and focuses on judgement-based operational HR support, local expertise, compliance, and operational execution rather than high-volume transactional query handling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Country HR Operations - Act as the operational HR lead for assigned country populations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex employee lifecycle activity including contractual changes, leave management, transfers, and local compliance processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure operational HR processes are delivered in line with local employment legislation and company standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation of global HR initiatives within country-specific legislative and operational frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Payroll, Benefits, HRIS, Finance and external vendors to suport compliant local delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Relations &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support employee relations matters including disciplinary, grievance, absence, performance, and workplace concerns in partnership with managers and HRBPs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide practical guidance on local employment legislation, policies, and operational risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate complex or high-risk matters appropriately to Regional Ops Lead or Legal team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain compliance with local labour law, working time obligations, statutory requirements, and internal governance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support audits, compliance reviews, and regulatory documentation requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business &amp;amp; Manager Support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide operational HR guidance to managers on employee lifecycle and country-specific people matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support operational delivery of organisational changes, restructures, transfers, and workforce actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HRBPs to operationalise business decisions and workforce changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure managers are supported through operational implementation of HR processes and policy application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational Governance &amp;amp; Improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify operational risks, processes, gaps, and opportunities for improvement or standardisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to development and maintenance of operational process documentation and country guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation of new HR systems, operational processes, and service delivery requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Education &amp;amp; Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration or related field preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional HR qualification (e.g. CIPD, SHRM, HRCI or equivalent) desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in relevant country-specific HR operational experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
