&lt;h2&gt;Role Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated, experienced Senior Data Analyst who will lead analytics efforts around Oncology patient journey, line of therapy (LoT) and structured claims/patient data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will transform large claims datasets into insights that shape strategic decisions for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and execute analytics projects focused on patient-journey and line-of-therapy mapping, Brand analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze structured claims and patient datasets such as DRG, IQVIA, McKesson, Symphony claims.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct exploratory data analysis (EDA) to assess treatment patterns, pathways and utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support HEOR/HCRU analyses including prevalence, burden, incidence and cost-of-illness studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and present client-facing insights using dashboards, PowerPoint and visual analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and optimise SQL queries, pipelines; use Excel and Python for automation and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with HEOR, market-access, strategy and engineering teams. Ability to gather requirements, articulate approach, timeline and execution with key stakeholders are of equal importance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data integrity, governance, documentation and reproducibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently manage workload, communicate progress and drive project delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years’ experience, with 3+ years in relevant analytics roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s/Master’s in Computer Science, Electronics, Pharmacy, Life Sciences, Data Science, Statistics or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior Experience with structured datasets: DRG, Symphony, IQVIA, McKesson.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in &lt;strong&gt;SQL, Python, Excel, PowerPoint&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Pharma/life-science consulting or analytics agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to RWE sources including EHR/EMR, CMS datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of LoT frameworks, treatment guidelines and market-access structures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Preferred / Nice to Haves&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Python and visualisation tools (Power BI, Tableau).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;understanding of &lt;strong&gt;data modeling&lt;/strong&gt; and statistical techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client-facing experience with ability to translate analytics into business insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Therapy-area familiarity (oncology, immunology, rare diseases).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience conducting stakeholder workshops or building interactive dashboards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working with global teams and multi-geography datasets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
